&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Compass, our mission is to help everyone find their place in the world. Founded in 2012, we’re revolutionizing the real estate industry with our end-to-end platform that empowers residential real estate agents to deliver exceptional service to seller and buyer clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive aka Strategic Growth Manager, you will be at the center of our growth strategy, directly responsible for driving net-new revenue across our company-owned brokerages, which may include Coldwell Banker, Sotheby’s International Realty, Corcoran, and Compass. You will partner with top-producing real estate agents—true CEOs of their own businesses—and influence them to grow their business with us.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will work alongside an incredibly high-performing and driven team, with colleagues coming from diverse and rigorous backgrounds including investment banking, management consulting, law, and enterprise sales. You’ll operate in a uniquely high-impact environment—our Strategic Growth Managers (SGMs) are conservatively generating 15x more revenue per head than top global tech firms, driven by the strength of our market, talent, and business momentum.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Drive strategic growth by identifying, engaging, and structuring deals with top-performing real estate agents and teams, expanding&amp;nbsp; our presence within your market. &lt;br&gt;-Position our value proposition including technology, marketing, culture, and growth platform. &lt;br&gt;-Build and manage a strong pipeline with a consultative and relationship-driven process. &lt;br&gt;-Develop deep market expertise and maintain a strong local presence. &lt;br&gt;-Collaborate with leadership, agents, and cross-functional teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What This Role Offers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Work directly with decision-makers for faster, high-impact conversations. &lt;br&gt;-Engage in a highly consultative, human sales process requiring high IQ and EQ. &lt;br&gt;-Build trusted relationships with high-performing professionals. &lt;br&gt;-Operate with high autonomy and ownership over your success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You’ll Be Measured&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a quota carrying role measured by revenue attainment. Deal sizes range from $75K to $5M+ with an average 30-day sales cycle.&amp;nbsp; Revenue is measured by agent, team and brokerage production volume.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in our Arlington (Washington Blvd.) office, this onsite, market-facing role will have you engaging clients in the field while collaborating in person with local teams and agents.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Bachelor’s degree with 5+ years of relevant experience &lt;br&gt;-Proven success in a quota-carrying role &lt;br&gt;-Strong interpersonal and communication skills &lt;br&gt;-Self-starter with strong judgment &lt;br&gt;-Highly organized with ability to manage multiple priorities &lt;br&gt;-Track record of high performance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base pay range for this position is $100,000–$110,000 annually, with a target bonus of $30,000–$60,000 and uncapped bonus potential. We provide a full range of benefits and compensation may include equity. Base pay is based on market location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks that You Need to Know About:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;f

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Compass, our mission is to help everyone find their place in the world. Founded in 2012, we’re revolutionizing the real estate industry with our end-to-end platform that empowers residential real estate agents to deliver exceptional service to seller and buyer clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our Strategic Growth team is the face of the company and the engine of our market expansion. As an Account Executive, AKA Strategic Growth Manager, you are directly responsible for driving net-new revenue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In its simplest form, the SGM’s role is to bring top producing agents to Compass by effectively selling the Compass value proposition (technology, marketing, culture and growth). Successful SGMs influence top agents to leave their current brokerage and join Compass. Since every agent is an independent contractor they can take their business wherever they receive the best value and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The refreshing part of this sale is that you are working directly with decision-makers, thus eliminating many of the hassles of selling to large corporations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a fully onsite role and will report into our Austin Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will spend a significant portion of your time meeting clients and prospects in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This market-based role focuses on high-impact engagement at our offices and in the field. You are expected in-person in your market to maximize collaboration with your local teams and agents on-site.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;METRICS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a quota carrying role. Your quota per quarter is metric’d by the amount of Gross Commission Income (GCI) you successfully bring to Compass. GCI is a way to quantify an agent and equates to the amount of commission an agent’s produced in the prior 12 month period. Our deal size is anywhere from $200k - $3M+, with an average time to close at about 30 days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can meet quota each quarter by bringing on a number of individual agents or large agent teams. Your quota is based on the prior 12 months performance of that agent or team. It is not contingent upon their future production once at Compass.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are tasked with helping agents understand why their business, and their clients, will benefit by moving to Compass.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NUANCES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a more humanized sale than your average sales process as you are dealing directly with decision makers. You can think of every agent as the CEO of their own business - with that comes a heightened degree of empathy needed to be successful in the sale, but also the ability for quick decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think about a top producing agent who’s been with a brokerage for 15+ years. Their personal and professional identity is often wrapped up in that brokerage’s brand. Successfully decoupling an agent from their prior brokerage takes outstanding patience, listening, agility and ultimate focus to get the deal done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The equally demanding need for high IQ and EQ in this role has resulted in an incredibly high performing and driven team of diverse backgrounds such as investment banking, management consulting, law and enterprise sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;By virtue of the space we are operating in, the talent on the team and the incredible momentum in our business, we are seeing our SGM’s conservatively generate 15x more revenue per head than the top tech firms in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B.A. or B.S. with 5+ years of relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills, glass-half-full mentality&

